post_text: Friends helping friends today...we got your back! When Hudson Community Schools called...DNH and Union responded. HUGE thanks to our DNH All-Star Nutrition staff who put together 130 sack lunches while also preparing lunch for 900 right here at home. In less than an hour, sack lunches were put together and then delivered so the students at Hudson could still be served their lunch at regular time. Union doing the same. And guess what??? Our kids still ate at their regular time! Can't beat the collective strength of the NICL Conference! Proud of our team. #BeTheStrength #rollblue #UKnighted #PirateRising

post_text:
Looking at the forecast for next week in our area, there will likely be several days with temperatures in the low- to mid-90s. As a result, Dike-New Hartford will have a two-hour early dismissal each day next week, August 24-28.

While we know Friday might look to provide some cooler temperatures, our past experience tells us our rooms will still be very hot.

We know that this change causes even more disruption to what is already a very challenging start to the school year due to COVID-19. Please know that we have made this decision in the interest of the health and safety of our students and staff.

We sincerely appreciate everyone's understanding and we look forward to a successful 2020-21 school year! #rollblue #BeTheStrength

post_text:
We would like to sincerely thank everyone who contributed to our meal service over the past several months! We would also like to thank our entire community for your patience and understanding as we've addressed the challenges of this unprecedented global health crisis.

From March 19 to August 8, we served 28,250 breakfasts and 28,250 lunches, for a total of 56,500 meals for kids! We could not have done it without the support of so many people in our district and community.

Once again, THANK YOU! #rollblue #BeTheStrength

post_text:
Central Rivers AEA has issued new substitute teacher guidelines for the 2020-21 school year. These include:

*AA degree or BA or 60 hours of coursework at a post secondary level
*Minimum of 20 years of age
*No limit to amount of days they can substitute
*Paras with Sub Authorization can sub in any classroom
*Paras need the Para Certification in order to be eligible for the Substitute Authorization
*Substitute Authorization is required to substitute teach unless the individual already has a license in good standing

To learn more, visit https://docs.google.com/document/d/1oOBPYCA4qURPhxnJWoDa5DoGbII6xRubp0c-BigqyTE/edit?ts=5f26ca0a.

post_text:
The Iowa Department of Human Services will distribute additional food assistance benefits to families throughout the state, including in the Dike-New Hartford Community School District.

The Families First CoronaVirus Act allows states to issue benefits to households with children in Pre-K through 12th grade that lost access to free and reduced-price school meals due to extended school closures last spring.

Eligible families will receive $307.80 per child. If your household received food assistance benefits in April, May or June, you will see that amount added to your EBT card by July 15. If you have not received food benefits in the past three months, you will get a P-EBT card in the mail before July 21.

The P-EBT cards will come in a white envelope addressed with your child's name, with a return address from Austin, TX. The cards themselves will be white with black font, with "IOWA P-EBT" printed at the top. Once you receive your card, follow the included instructions to activate it.

Learn more: https://dhs.iowa.gov/P-EBT

The school district has been informed that a member of the baseball coaching staff has been tested for COVID-19 after it was discovered that he was in close contact with an individual who has a confirmed case of the virus.

As a result, tonight's game against Hudson will be cancelled. There will also be no baseball practices or games until the test results are known.

As we follow the recommendations from the Iowa Department of Public Health, please know that we are acting out of an abundance of caution to protect the health and well-being of our student-athletes, coaches, and families. At this time, there have been no reports of any other illnesses or symptoms experienced by any other coach or team member.

I know that this news is disappointing, but we hope to allow our team to get back on the field soon. We will keep you updated as soon as we learn more. Thank you.

Previously scheduled DNH softball games will be held as scheduled.

As we follow the recommendations from the Iowa Department of Public Health, please know that we are acting out of an abundance of caution to protect the health and well-being of our student-athletes, coaches, and families. At this time, there have been no reports of any other illnesses or symptoms experienced by any other coach or team member.

I know that this news is disappointing, but we hope to allow our team to get back on the field soon. We will keep you updated as soon as we learn more. Thank you.

Previously scheduled DNH softball games will be held as scheduled.

GRADUATION UPDATE: DNH will hold an in-person graduation ceremony in the auditorium on Sunday, June 28 at 2 p.m.!

Previously, we planned to hold graduation outdoors. However, we have decided to move the event back to the auditorium, which is more secure and offers protection from potential rain.

Each graduate will be limited to four guests. The ceremony will also be live-streamed on the DNH YouTube channel so our families and community members can watch from home.

Along with allowing them to receive their diploma, the ceremony will be many of our seniors' final school-related function as students of DNH. We look forward to bringing them together one final time and will make this event as special and memorable as possible! #rollblue

Unfortunately, DNH students will not be able to undergo physicals at the high school during the summer, as in previous years.

The IHSAA and IGHSAU have granted an extension on all expiring physicals through July 25. After July 25, however, students will need a new physical to participate.

Earlier today, Governor Reynolds announced that summer sports may begin June 1.

After the announcement, the Iowa Department of Education provided school districts with guidance regarding the rules and restrictions that will apply to summer sports. We are now reviewing that guidance and will communicate with DNH student-athletes and families once we have made some key decisions on next steps.

Above all else, the safety of our student-athletes is our top priority.

In the meantime, we want to thank everyone for their continued patience. We will follow up soon with more information. #rollblue

shared_text:
Honoring Our Fallen is in Dike, Iowa.
May 18 at 4:56 PM Â· Dike, IA Â·

Mission Complete--PFC Tyler Cox made his final journey home to Iowa on Wednesday and today he was laid to rest with military honors!

Cox, 19, of Dike, died unexpectedly in a training accident on Wednesday, April 29th at Camp LeJeune in Jacksonville, North Carolina, where he was stationed. He had been assigned to a 3rd Battalion 8th Marines as a 0311 Rifleman.

PFC Cox returned home to Iowa on Wednesday 13 May to his family. His family appreciates all who came out to honor Tyler last night it means so much to see him honored.

Tyler was born on July 21, 2000. He attended school in Dike and was able to graduate early from Dike-New Hartford High School to enlist in the United States Marine Corps Tragically, Tylerâ€™s life was cut short at the tender age of 19 but his family was so proud of Tylerâ€™s willingness to serve his country.

#HonoringOurFallen #AHeroRememberedNeverDies #Saytheirnames

post_text:
Last month, we lost a member of our DNH community when PFC Tyler Cox died in a training accident at Camp LeJeune in North Carolina.

Tyler will be coming home Wednesday evening. If you would like to honor him, there will be a memorial escort that will begin at approximately 10 p.m. after the original flight lands in Des Moines around 8 p.m.

From Highway 20, the escort will head north on First Street in Dike, right on Monroe Street and then right on Main Street to the funeral chapel. Please feel free to line the side streets to show your support, while maintaining social distancing.

Tyler's funeral service will be Saturday at 11 a.m. at the DNH High School Auditorium. Attendance at the service will be limited due to COVID-19.

We are deeply saddened by this loss. We hope you can join us in honoring Tyler and celebrating the wonderful impact he had on his family, his friends and our entire community.

We received a surprise today!

As we continue to find ways to celebrate Teacher Appreciation Week, our students wanted to be sure you knew how they felt!

Our learning curve has been really steep, but everyone has embraced it with open arms. We're also finding ways to laugh at ourselves as we've transitioned (overnight) into an online learning environment.

Please enjoy this video from our students as they present lighthearted moments from the past few months and give thanks to their teachers for everything they do! #rollblue

post_text:
It is with a great deal of sadness that we share with you that Janeen Danielsen, who was well known in our DNH communities, has passed away. She was 80 years old.

Janeen served on the Dike Board of Education for 15 years. She was also a member of the AEA Board and served as wedding coordinator at United Church of Christ in Cedar Falls.

Janeen's husband, Dale, currently serves a substitute bus driver in our district after retiring following many years as a full time driver.

Dale and Janeen were married nearly 62 years. The family will be holding a private funeral service in Dike.

Please join us in keeping the Danielsens, their family, and their friends in your thoughts.

Obituary-https://www.richardsonfuneralservice.com/obituaries/Janeen-Danielsen/#!/PhotosVideos

post_text:
UPDATE: School is running as scheduled tomorrow before closing on Tuesday until further notice. Tonight, Governor Reynolds recommended that schools in Iowa close for the next four weeks. We will continue to evaluate this on a week to week basis.

No before or after school activities tomorrow (Monday, March 16th). From Tuesday through Friday this week, all buildings will be closed and all activities will be cancelled until further notice.

We are confident our preventive measures to clean and disinfect will allow us to hold classes as scheduled tomorrow. That being said, if you choose to keep your child home, we will support that. Simply call your child's building and report the absence.

We'll continue to post information on multiple platforms as it becomes available. Thank you for your patience.

GOVERNOR'S FULL STATEMENT: https://governor.iowa.gov/press-release/gov-reynolds-recommends-iowa-schools-close-for-four-weeks-will-hold-a-press-0

post_text:
Tonight, the Dike-New Hartford School District community approved the school bond question on the ballot. Unofficial results show 70% support.

We are driven to provide the best possible academic opportunities for our students. The approved bond will allow Dike-New Hartford Community Schools to continue to do just that, while ensuring the long-term viability of our district.

We would like to thank everyone who participated in this process, including those who provided us with their feedback and input over the past several months.

We appreciate our community's support and look forward to continuing these important conversations about the future of our schools. #rollblue
